## handoff
- produced: full-stack e-commerce demo — Node.js+TS backend LISTENING on port 3742 (Surface), Vite+React frontend built to `public/demos/orschell-excavating-e-commerce-full/`, bridge blueprint written to `mw-backend/orschell_ecommerce_blueprint.py` (registered in server.py, NOT pushed), workSamples.js entry added (id 18)
- decisions: HashRouter (GH Pages SPA); bridge strips `accept-encoding` to prevent gzip mismatch; node:sqlite with DatabaseSync (no gyp, Node 22); 22 REST endpoints; atomic inventory decrement via UPDATE quantity-= WHERE quantity>=
- next needs: deploy step must push mw-backend (bridge goes live ~30s after push) AND push michaelwegter.com (GH Pages builds frontend); then verify GET /demos/orschell-excavating-e-commerce-full/api/health returns ok AND the demo URL loads
- risks: mw-backend push required before bridge is live; if Surface service crashes, re-run surface_register.py (idempotent); recharts adds bundle weight but build succeeded
